per chromatin","Highly pleomorphic cells with giant cells and frequent mitoses","Uniform follicular cells arranged in colloid-filled follicles"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe histological features of thyroid carcinomas are distinct and help in classification and prognosis:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHighly pleomorphic cells with giant cells and frequent mitoses\u003C/strong\u003E are characteristic of anaplastic thyroid carcinoma, reflecting its poor differentiation and aggressive nature\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EUniform follicular cells arranged in colloid-filled follicles\u003C/strong\u003E describe normal thyroid tissue or well-differentiated follicular lesions\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPapillary structures with ground glass nuclei\u003C/strong\u003E are typical of papillary thyroid carcinoma\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESmall uniform cells with salt-and-pepper chromatin\u003C/strong\u003E are seen in medullary thyroid carcinoma\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHurthle cells with abundant eosinophilic cytoplasm\u003C/strong\u003E are found in Hurthle cell neoplasms\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAnaplastic thyroid carcinoma is the most undifferentiated and aggressive form of thyroid cancer, with cells showing marked pleomorphism, numerous mitotic figures, and areas of necrosis.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Anaplastic thyroid carcinoma shows marked cellular pleomorphism, giant cells, and high mitotic activity.","Anaplastic thyroid carcinoma is the most aggressive form of thyroid cancer with poor differentiation."],"references":["Shah JP. Thyroid carcinoma: epidemiology, histology, and diagnosis. Clin Adv Hematol Oncol. 2015 Apr;13(4 Suppl 4):3-6. PMID: 26430868; PMCID: PMC5526593","Kitahara CM, Schneider AB. Epidemiology of Thyroid Cancer. Cancer Epidemiol Biomarkers Prev. 202